thread.title: WA councillor lashes parking company

title: WA councillor lashes parking company
text:
Thu, Aug 27, 2015, 7:12 PM AEST - Australia Markets closed WA councillor lashes parking company AAP – 4 hours ago Print 
An affluent Perth council is trying to tear up a contract with a multinational parking corporation, with one councillor labelling the company "corporate psychopaths". 
Mark Burns from the City of Subiaco said Wilson Parking, which manages 46 bays on Sneddon Street, had three people watching "like hawks" to fine over-stayers $65 and that he didn't want to be in bed with a company that made the area look bad. 
"They meet every criteria of a psychopath," Mr Burns told AAP. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Dairy price plunge hurts Bega Cheese AAP
